Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 07:16:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: stats + achievements data layer, ESM bundling, CI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Source modules (pure logic, no UI yet):
- src/stats/queries.js: computeStats({characters, threads, messages, lore})
  -> stats bundle. Pure fn; IDB access deliberately lives elsewhere so this
  layer is unit-testable in Node.
- src/achievements/tiers.js: XP/level math with quadratic level curve.
  Level 1 free, level 2 at 100 XP, level 10 at 8100, level 50 at 240k.
  No grind-to-max by design.
- src/achievements/registry.js: 15 starter achievements, tiered common ->
  uncommon -> rare -> epic. All narrative-focused: words written, thread
  depth, cast breadth, worldbuilding, distinct active days. Explicitly
  documented: days-active counts distinct days with user activity, not
  sessions/time-on-site.
- src/achievements/unlocks.js: computeUnlockedIds(stats) + diffNewUnlocks
  for detecting newly-unlocked between calls.
- src/utils/escape.js: HTML escape helper for future UI work.

Build:
- ESM keyword stripping added to build/build.mjs. Source files are
  authored as ESM so Node tests can import them directly; the bundler
  strips export/import keywords so the concatenated IIFE is valid plain
  <script>. Stripper handles the common forms we use.
- Bundle metadata no longer includes a build timestamp (made builds
  non-deterministic; broke idempotence test). Filesystem mtime suffices.
- src/manifest.json now lists the 5 modules in dependency order.

Tests (node --test, 32 total, all green):
- test/stats_queries.test.mjs: empty stats, word counting edge cases,
  user-only word totals, longest-thread logic, distinct-day counting,
  first/last activity timestamps, defensiveness against malformed data.
- test/achievements.test.mjs: xpFromStats weighting, level curve
  monotonicity, progress01 bounds, registry integrity (unique IDs, valid
  tiers, required fields), computeUnlockedIds tier progression, sorted
  output, diffNewUnlocks semantics.
- test/build.test.mjs: two new assertions for populated-manifest path —
  verifies bundle header appears, NS wrapper present, module markers
  present, and that ESM keywords were stripped from output.

CI:
- .github/workflows/ci.yml: runs 'npm test' and 'npm run build:check' on
  pushes and PRs to main. No 'npm ci' step since project has zero deps.

Architecture:
- docs/architecture.md: extension points corrected. Mini-card mounts at
  #leftColumn (sidebar), before the #newThreadButton row — always-visible
  ambient progress UI. Selector anchors we depend on are now documented
  explicitly so future upstream syncs know what to smoke-check.
